83rd OREGON LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY--2026 Regular Session
House Bill 4068
Introduced and printed pursuant to House Rule 12.00. Presession filed (at the request of House Interim Committee
on Behavioral Health for Representative Hai Pham)
SUMMARY
The following summary is not prepared by the sponsors of the measure and is not a part of the body thereof subject
to consideration by the Legislative Assembly. It is an editor’s brief statement of the essential features of the
measure as introduced. The statement includes a measure digest written in compliance with applicable readability
standards.
Digest: The Act changes the age range for young adults to be considered transition aged youth
for purposes of a program in OHA. (Flesch Readability Score: 61.4).
Modifies the definition of “transition aged youth residential treatment home” to include young
adults between the ages of 17 and 25.
Declares an emergency, effective on passage.
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT
2 Relating to residential treatment homes for transition aged youth; amending section 2, chapter 560,
3 Oregon Laws 2025; and declaring an emergency.
4 Be It Enacted by the People of the State of Oregon:
5 SECTION 1. Section 2, chapter 560, Oregon Laws 2025, is amended to read:
6 Sec. 2. (1) As used in this section:
7 (a) “Facility” means:
8 (A) A residential treatment facility;
9 (B) A residential treatment home;
10 (C) A secure residential treatment facility; or
11 (D) A secure residential treatment home.
12 (b) “Residential treatment facility” has the meaning given that term in ORS 443.400.
13 (c) “Residential treatment home” has the meaning given that term in ORS 443.400.
14 (d) “Secure residential treatment facility” means a facility described in ORS 443.465.
15 (e) “Secure residential treatment home” means a home described in ORS 443.465.
16 (f) “Transition aged youth residential treatment home” means a residential treatment home for
17 young adults between the ages of [17.5] 17 and 25 years of age who experience complex behavioral
18 health challenges.
19 (2) The Oregon Health Authority shall adopt rules to:
20 (a) Support facilities in developing early transition plans for residents.
21 (b) Establish a separate licensing process for transition aged youth residential treatment homes.
22 (3) No later than September 15, 2025, the authority shall submit an interim report, in the manner
23 provided in ORS 192.245, to the interim committees of the Legislative Assembly related to health,
24 about the authority’s progress in carrying out the provisions of this section and any recommen-
25 dations for needed legislative changes.
26 (4) No later than September 15, 2026, the authority shall submit a final report, in the manner
27 provided in ORS 192.245, to the interim committees of the Legislative Assembly related to health,
28 about the authority’s progress in carrying out the provisions of this section and any recommen-
